Medya yÃ¼klenemedi. I bought these trainers as a direct replacement for another pair of mid-budget Terrex trainers that had provided years of service. Initially they were great but after a few minutes wearing they develop a squeaking/clicking noise that is truly unbearable. It doesn't happen immediately but after a few minutes, when the materials or adhesives begin to warm up it starts and then there's no stopping it. I've cleaned the sole, cleaned the inner, tried a new insole, tried different socks but nothing can stop the squeak. I suspect it's a manufacturing defect with the rubber composition or an issue with the glues between the layers of sole materials. Either way, although these are outside their return time, I'm going to try sending them back. I wore them in a Spanish museum recently and they caused such a noise that I ended up taking them off and walking around in just my socks.

After a decade of being required to wear tactical or hiking boots to work I decided I try something different when I changed careers so I picked up a pair of these. They are very comfortable and definitely some of the best athletic shoes I've ever owned. Now, when I first bought them and put them on, they were super tight on my foot, to the point I thought they were too small, but after about an hour or two with them on, the insoles had molded to the shape of my foot and they fit perfectly now. I love how they look and I love how lightweight they are.
